					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It is possible I imagine. But it would probably make more sense to use a single 27C322 with some other chips to replace the original maskrom on the original cartridge instead. The ROMLAB site had stuff about swapping SRAM chips but there could be errors in the diagrams, I have no idea. If you just want to play the game, a Tototek or MashMods flash cartridge would be a much more simple and useful solution to playing it on real hardware. Building repros is relatively expensive compared to a reusable device like a Flash Cartridge, PowerPAK, or old style Copier unit.</div>

